amarantin
=========

HistFactory fit library
-----------------------
The preferred persisted downstream analysis surface is still `DistributionIO`,
but the fit implementation is now a ROOT `RooStats::HistFactory` measurement
built directly in memory from cached spectra. No second native minimizer path
remains in the library.

The small public surface is:
  - `fit::ProcessKind`
  - `fit::Spec`
  - `fit::Process`
  - `fit::Channel`
  - `fit::Problem`
  - `fit::FitOptions`
  - `fit::Result`
  - `fit::ChannelResult`
  - `fit::make_independent_problem(...)`
  - `fit::profile_signal_strength(...)`

Typical workflow:

  build/bin/mk_fit \
    --manifest numu_signal_region.fit.manifest \
    --output build/fits/numu_signal_region.fit.txt \
    build/dists/final.dists.root \
    numu_signal_region

Single-channel manifest rows are:

  process-name kind sample-key [cache-key]

Rows with kind `data` fill the observed bins automatically. Without manifest
data rows, pass `--data-bins` or use `--allow-zero-data` when an empty
observation is intentional.

Combined SR/CR-style manifests use one explicit fit-channel token per row:

  fit-channel process-name kind sample-key cache-key

Use `-` for the cache-key column when the first cached entry for that sample is
the intended one.

For programmatic use, `app/mk_fit.cc` remains the reference path behind the
`mk_fit` CLI for turning cached `DistributionIO::Spectrum` payloads into one or
more `fit::Channel` objects.

The fit library expects one unique non-data process name per channel.

A `fit::Problem` now describes one HistFactory measurement:
  - each `fit::Channel` becomes one HistFactory channel
  - every process tagged `kSignal` shares the same POI
  - `sumw2` drives HistFactory MC-stat nuisances
  - family modes, detector shifts/templates, GENIE knob pairs, and envelope
    fallbacks become HistFactory shape systematics

The default builder still prefers richer cached payloads first:
  - family eigenmodes
  - family covariance-derived modes
  - diagonal sigma-only family fallback
  - explicit detector source shifts
  - explicit GENIE knob-pair source shifts
  - detector templates
  - detector envelopes
  - final `total_down` / `total_up` fallback only when no richer payload is
    present for that process

The combined fit report now records one fitted prediction block per channel when
the manifest defines more than one fit channel.

There is now a direct combined-channel smoke in `tests/fit_histfactory_smoke.cc`
that exercises a shared-nuisance SR+CR fit without going through the larger
shell fixture path.
